      • trimUnneccessaryVariables

        public static <StubHandle> Stub<StubHandle> trimUnneccessaryVariables(Buildable<?,StubHandle,?> buildable,
                                                      Stub<StubHandle> stub,
                                                      boolean onlyIfNotDetermined)
        Reduces the number of tuples by trimming (existentially quantifying) the set of variables that
        • are in the tuple,
        • are not exported parameters,
        • have all their constraints already enforced,
        and thus will not be needed anymore.
        Parameters:
        onlyIfNotDetermined - if true, no trimming performed unless there is at least one such variable
        Returns:
        the stub after the trimming (possibly the original)
